Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Mix chicken, cream of chicken soup, celery, rice, mayonnaise, eggs, lemon juice, onion, and salt in a large bowl. Transfer mixture to a 9x13-inch baking dish. Mix corn flakes and margarine in another bowl; sprinkle over chicken mixture. Bake in preheated oven until bubbly and golden brown, 40 to 45 minutes.